---
3md: 1.0
axis: row
title: Diagonal Garter Dishcloth
yarn: worsted cotton, approx 50g
needles: US 7 (4.5 mm)
gauge: not critical
abbreviations: k = knit, yo = yarn over, k2tog = knit two together, st = stitch
---
A classic corner-to-corner garter dishcloth. You increase one stitch each row
until the diagonal is wide enough, then decrease back down to a corner. Stitch
grids below: `|` = a garter stitch, `O` = the yarn-over eyelet edge.

@plane z=0 label="Cast on and setup"
# Setup

Cast on **4 stitches**. This is the bottom corner.

```
start corner:  | | | |   (4 st)
```

Knit one plain row to set up. Then move to the increase phase at [[z=1]].

@plane z=1 label="Increase rows"
# Increase Section (repeat until 44 st)

Work this single increase row over and over:

> **k2, yo, k to end.**

The `yo` makes the eyelet border and adds one stitch per row.

```
row  6:  O | | | | |        (6 st)
row 10:  O | | | | | | | |  (10 st)
row 20:  O | | | | | ...    (20 st)
```

- Keep going until you have **44 stitches** on the needle.
- The piece is now a growing triangle. The yarn-over edge is always on the same side.

When you hit 44 st, switch to the turning row at [[z=2|the center turn]].

@plane z=2 label="Center turn"
# Center Turning Row

This is the widest point, the diagonal corner-to-corner line.

> Turning row: **k1, k2tog, yo, k2tog, k to end.**

This row both increases (the yo) and decreases twice, so the count drops by one.
After this row you should have **43 stitches**.

```
center line:  O | | | | | | ... | |   (widest)
```

Now the triangle starts shrinking. Continue to decreases at [[z=3]].

@plane z=3 label="Decrease rows"
# Decrease Section (repeat until 6 st)

Work this decrease row repeatedly:

> **k1, k2tog, yo, k2tog, k to end.**

You still make a yo (to keep the eyelet edge matching) but the double decrease
shrinks the row by one stitch each time.

```
row -10:  O | | | | | ...   (30 st)
row -20:  O | | | | |       (16 st)
row -30:  O | | |           (6 st)
```

Continue until **6 stitches** remain. Then finish at [[z=4|bind off]].

@plane z=4 label="Bind off and finish"
# Finishing

1. Last row: **k1, k2tog, k2tog, k1** to bring it down to **4 stitches**.
2. Bind off all 4 stitches.
3. Cut the yarn leaving a 15 cm tail.
4. Weave in both tails (cast-on and bind-off) with a tapestry needle.

```
finished square (schematic):
  +---------+
  | / / / / |   garter ridges run on the diagonal
  | / / / / |
  +---------+
```

You now have a square dishcloth. To make another size, just change the target
stitch count in [[z=1|the increase section]] (more stitches = bigger cloth).
